The SQL Server (Transact-SQL) >= (greater than or equal to) operator checks if the value of left operand is greater than or equal to the value of right operand and returns true if the condition is true, false otherwise.

Syntax
The syntax for using greater than or equal to operator in SQL Server (Transact-SQL) is given below:

expression >= expression 

To select records of table where Age of the person is greater than or equal to 27, the query is given below.

SELECT * FROM Employee
WHERE Age >= 27;
